 About the author
 ANNA SPARRMAN is Assistant Professor at the Department of Child Studies at Linköping
 University, Sweden. Her PhD explored children’s (6 /8 years of age) interaction with
 visual culture in everyday life. Her current research interests include visual culture,
 critical discourse analysis and children’s/youth’s agency. A current research project
 concerns youths’ (15 /18 years of age) classroom discussions about popular films run by
 the Swedish School Cinema programme. Film as an educational device as well as young
 people’s notions of societal issues are explored.
