n with visual culture in everyday life. Her current research interests include visual culture, critical discourse analysis and children&#39;s/youth&#39;s agency. A current research project concerns youths&#39; (15 Á/18 years of age) classroom discussions about popular films run by the Swedish School Cinema programme. Film as an educational device as well as young people&#39;s notions of societal issues are explored.</li></ol><button class="ds2-5-button ds2-5-button--extra-small ds2-5-button--full-width js-tc-loswp--references-view-more references--view-more-link" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.add(&#39;references--show-all&#39;);">View more<span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size: 20px" translate="no">arrow_downward</span></button><script data-cfasync="false" src="/cdn-cgi/scripts/5c5dd728/cloudflare-static/email-decode.min.js"></script><script>document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
